cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.LG, cs.BIO, cs.DM 

This paper is primarily focused on developing an algorithmic solution for a computational problem related to genome assembly. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with graph theory and computational biology, which makes cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.BIO (Bioinformatics) likely sub-categories as well. The paper's algorithmic approach and analysis also involve concepts from computational complexity theory, which makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on genome assembly and sequencing data analysis makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category, although it is less likely than the other four.
